OL,3,CWhat are potholes costing motorists ?
OL,4,CNew data exposes depth of problem
OL,6,FMeanwhile the AA reports 1,700 cars
OL,7,Fneeding repairs each day - and an
OL,8,Foverall annual cost of #597 million.
OL,10,FVehicle tax, fuel tax, congestion and
OL,11,Femissions charges - many motorists
OL,12,Ffeel fleeced especially when you see
OL,13,Fwhat they're getting.
OL,15,FPotholes might be largely created by
OL,16,Fthe forces of nature - but councils
OL,17,Fare also blamed.
OL,19,FThere are too many temporary patch-ups
OL,20,Fsay the experts and when councils make
OL,21,Fsavings motorists often pay the price.
